Message.MsgText: ADMK0203E=ADMK0203E: Unmanaged node's platform type must be one of: os400, aix, hpux, linux, solaris, windows, os390
Message.Explanation: The platform type specified is not a recognized type.
Message.UserResponse: Specify one of the recognized platform types and resubmit the command.

Message.MsgText: ADMK0206E=ADMK0206E: Only one unmanaged node may be added to standalone systems.
Message.Explanation: Only one unmanaged node may be added to stand alone systems.
Message.UserResponse: Do not add the unmanaged node to the system.

Message.MsgText: ADMK0204E=ADMK0204E: The node you are attempting to create already exists in your workspace.
Message.Explanation: The node cannot be created because a node of the same name already exists.
Message.UserResponse: Do one of the following actions: Create a node with a different name; or, to create the existing node again, first remove it, then create it.

Message.MsgText: ADMK0207E=ADMK0207E: The command is not supported in job manager. You need to use queryManagedNodes command.
Message.Explanation: The command is not supported in job manager environment.
Message.UserResponse: You need to use queryManagedNodes command.

Message.MsgText: ADMK0202E=ADMK0202E: removeUnManagedNode should only be used to remove an unmanaged node. {0} is a managed node. No changes were made.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to remove a managed node using the removeUnmanagedNode command. The removeUnmanagedNode command can be used to remove unmanaged nodes only. The specified managed node was not removed.
Message.UserResponse: Use the administrative console or the removeNode command to remove a managed node.

Message.MsgText: ADMK0205E=ADMK0205E: Base version of node must be of form: w.y.z.n where w, y, z, and n are integers.
Message.Explanation: The base version of the node must be of the form: w.y.z.n , where w, y, z, and n are integers.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a correct value and resubmit the command.
